x4freetext: Michigan State University using the K1200 cyclotron.
<= 8 were measured with the Large Area Silicon Strip
Detector Array (LASSA), an array consisting of
nine telescopes, each composed of one 65 mu-m thick
and one 500 mu-m Si strip detector, followed by four
60-mm-thick CsI(Tl) detectors. The 50 x 50 mm2 area
of each LASSA telescope was divided by the strips
of the second silicon detector into 256
3 x 3 mm2 square pixels, providing an angular
resolution of about 0.43deg. The LASSA was centered
at a polar angle of 32deg with respect to the beam
axis, providing coverage at polar angles of 7deg <=
At larger angles, charged particles were
detectors of the Michigan State University Miniball
and Washington University Miniwall array, which
together subtended a range of polar angles of 7deg <=

x4freetext: Energy spectra were measured for central collisions.

multiplicity of charged particles, which was
determined for each reaction event. Energy spectra
